Usage
=======

$ ./swap_test.py -h
usage: swap_test.py [-h] [--phi {00,01,10,11,random}]

Swap test for a 2-qbit input

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --phi {00,01,10,11,random}
                        input vector selection (default=01)


Sample Run
============
$ ./swap_test.py -n 4



Notes
=======
This is a specialized version of the Hadamard test, but instead of using a
random n x n unitary matrix, it uses the 2 x 2 swap matrix. Final result is
printed to standard output, whilst intermediates are printed to standard error.
Printing intermediates relies on numpy.
